        <h2>Safety Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Always be aware of your surroundings.</li>
            <li>Trust your instincts – if something feels wrong, act on it.</li>
            <li>Carry a self-defense tool such as pepper spray.</li>
            <li>Share your location with trusted contacts when traveling alone.</li>
            <li>Use apps or services designed for women’s safety, such as SOS or emergency alert apps.</li>
